---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Web Application Testing | Sheepdog Cyber Defense" description="Web application penetration testing for Texas businesses. Find vulnerabilities in your web apps and APIs before attackers do.">
  <section>
    <h1>Web Application Testing</h1>
    <p class="lead">Your web applications are often the most exposed part of your organization. We find the bugs before the attackers do.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What It Covers</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Custom web applications</li>
      <li>REST and GraphQL APIs</li>
      <li>Authentication and authorization</li>
      <li>Session management</li>
      <li>Data validation</li>
      <li>Third-party integrations</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Our Approach</h2>
    <p>We combine automated scanning with manual testing. We look for OWASP Top 10 issues, logic flaws, and business-specific vulnerabilities that scanners miss.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Deliverables</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Detailed findings report</li>
      <li>Reproduction steps for each finding</li>
      <li>Remediation guidance</li>
      <li>Executive summary</li>
      <li>Retest option available</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Typical Timeline</h2>
    <p>Web app tests vary widely based on complexity. A standard application takes 1-2 weeks. We'll provide an estimate upon scope review.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What You'll Need</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>URLs or access to staging/production</li>
      <li>API documentation</li>
      <li>Test accounts (as needed)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <a href="/contact" class="btn">Request a Quote</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .lead { font-size: 1.25rem; max-width: 700px; }
  section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .cta { padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
</style>
